      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A 42-year-old patient is undergoing a renal physiology assessment. The specific nephrons in different parts of kidneyare responsible for creating osmotic gradients in the kidneys and play a central role in renal function. Which of the following are mainly involved in the creation of osmotic </span></span><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">gradients<span style=\"color:black\"> in the </span>kidneys<span style=\"color:black\">?</span></span></span></span></p>",
